The paper deals with auction theory and mechanism design, which are central topics in game theory and economics. Therefore, cs.GT (Game Theory) and cs.EC (Economics and Computation) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves analyzing the efficiency and revenue of different auction mechanisms, which requires algorithmic and computational techniques, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. Finally, the paper involves analyzing the behavior of bidders in different auction mechanisms, which is a topic in machine learning and statistics, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible sub-category.
